07/02/2011
WASHINGTON, United States -- Serbian Deputy Prime Minister Ivica Dacic offered Serbia's assistance in fighting drug trafficking during a meeting with Drug Enforcement Administration (DEA) Director Michele Leonheart in Washington, Serbian media reported on Saturday (February 5th).
Dacic proposed Belgrade host a regional conference on combating the drug trade.
Both agreed that bilateral co-operation is very good in this field.
(Tanjug, RTS - 05/02/11)
